caption: Great food
A preferred spot for american food. Staff treated us so nice. Reminds me of a cafe in Chicago I liked to visit.

One of my favorite breakfast spots until recently. Ordered an omlette and got bad avacado on 2 occasions, coffee was weak and only a 3/4 of a cup, potatoes burnt, missing toast. Called when I got home and the server said to expect a call from the manager. Never received a call back. I won't be going back here and will inform others of the downtrend until I hear back from management. I feel disrespected. Been a resident of Wicker Park for the past 20 years. Get your shtuff together Bongo!!
My fav spot for quality American food. It's so appetizing. Fast and courteous service. It has a nice atmosphere.
Loved the Chocolate French toast but $19 after taxes for a French toast seems a bit pricey!
Soooo good!
Whenever I visit chicago, I have to eat here. They have the most unique pancakes
Great mimosas and the chocolate tower french toast was good too!
American food and service here is very good. Cool place to meet and catch up with coworkers. The service was very welcoming and observant.
Amazing food I love this place.
Food was delicious as usual. We've been customers for over 20 years now. Tables well-spaced apart. All employees were wearing masks. They checked our temperature when we arrived.
Found this Breakfast/Brunch spot on the Eaters List of essential breakfast places. The Wicker Park location is a cozy & quaint spot with fast friendly service.
American food and the setting at this place is super good. Will surely make a return trip.
Best breakfast in Chicago

As always a great place.  As always the Breakfast Burrito my face, but its really a more exciting sweet breakfast spot if you like sweet breakfast!!! Today's fruit plate was the most fruit I ever got (a weekday or covid residual)?  I prefer to go during the week and let all the others have the weekend!  There is extensive construction happening on Milwaukee  Street, but I was diligent and able to find a park!   One of the best things I did today.
Their pancake is always amazing. The egg burrito was a little underwhelming
One of my top spots for quality American food. Nothing to complain about. It has a great atmosphere. Menu is like a place in San Francisco I loved.

Cool, cozy, and lively restaurant. Ambience is fun and hip. Friends and family make the dining experience great here. Breakfast items are delicious. Simple eggs of any style with potatoes and toasts are excellent choices here in addition to avocado plates. Friendly staffs.
Bongo room has most amazing Benedicts as well as great desert style pancakes and French toast.
Too pricey for what it was

Delicious food and great service. My sister and I split the beef and crimini mushroom omelet with garlic herb butter and the cinnamon apple pancakes with maple mascarpone topping. We will definitely be back!
Service here was good, as well as the food!
Sweet breakfast is fantastic! Need a few more solid savory options

Delicious food. It is a bit pricey but it never feels like my money was wasted. The portions are huge. My suggestion is to order a couple things and get side plates for sharing. Get something with the vanilla bean or butter pecan sauce. Omg. Had the burrito bowl. It was fantastic..not that spicy though would love more heat.
Great food and great service
Good food
Great food and great service
Really great food, good coffee, great service. My kids love this place.
If you’re a fan of shrimp you must try the shrimp scampi eggs Benedict 🍤 🍤
Pancakes, flapjacks are phenomenal! You can even get a half order. Hash browns are a must

Wife and I stopped in while in town. I ordered the Chorizo, Avocado & Potato omelette, wife also had an omelette. Neither of us could finish our food we were so displeased, which for me is almost never. I am not sure how anything with Chorizo in it could be bland. Wife had the same impression with her omelette. Both thought the potatoes on the side were also flavorless, despite looking like they should have been delicious.
Fairly mediocre given the outrageous prices. This is brunch culture at its worst

Good brunch food and decent service, I enjoyed it and would come back here. I tried the gingerbread and pear french toast which I thought were very good. Also sampled their croissant sandwich which I also liked.
Great food, good service!
Great place for breakfast or lunch.  The atmosphere is inviting, and the food is constantly good.  Hearty portions.
Very rich and delicious food. Their pancakes are so decked out and flavorful! The restaurant is somewhat cramped with long wait times.

The Bongo Room is my favorite breakfast place, but they stopped selling my favorite pancakes with the cream sauce and bananas. Currently pregnant that’s what I have been craving! I hope they bring that dish back! Other than that, friendly staff and delicious coffee! Lunch is delicious!
Great food.
Great food Mamosa‘s we’re also good the citrus cocktail was excellent I did not give five stars because I found the price to be a bit much it’s not like we’re downtown also Service was great
(Translated by Google) Delicious breakfast with the family ...  (Original) Sehr leckeres Frühstück mit der Familie...

The waiter was rude and didn't listen we asked him 3 times about we needed straws he never bring them we went to the counter and got it. we gave a good tip.the food wasn't good only 2 ordered was good 2 wasn't .priced to high.
Great service, fabulous food and awesome atmosphere!!!  Can't wait to go again, so much more I want to try!!!

Bongo Room has an awesome menu with many different items to choose from. They offer both breakfast and lunch. My cousin recommended this place for their white chocolate pretzel pancakes. I did not try that one, but I did try the pumpkin spice pancake with vanilla sauce and cookie crumble on top. It was the perfect mixture between sweet and savory. I also ordered the vegetarian croissant sandwich. I thought it was good. A little messy because of the egg that bursted into my hand  but worth it!! The potatoes that came with it were soft, not very crunchy on the outside if that is what you like. We also tried the chorizo, potato and avocado omelette. It had a lot of mexican flavour. We enjoyed ourselves and would go back again. The service was great!
The food was delicious with such a variety of healthy choices! Breakfast was the best! Service was also good and friendly and the seating was very comfortable. Lots of good food.

I got there around 10:45 on a Sunday morning, and had about a 10 minute wait. I sat at the bar, maybe that's why my wait was short. The service was great. I ordered the deconstructed lobster benedict and a dill bloody mary. Both were very good, 1 egg was a little overcooked. I was trying something new. I enjoyed both. Overall I had a very good experience.
BREAKFAST!! worth the wait and the calories

The Bongo Room is one of my go-to Saturday Brunch spots. They have great service and better food. The brunch menu is constantly changing. My favorite thing to do is get a dish and split a side of pancakes. The pancakes are amazing! My only advice is to show up early. By 10-10:30am Saturday morning the place is packed with a long wait.
Great brunch option and friendly staff. Perfect for a lunch date or an afternoon hang with friends.
Amazing food and great coffee.. Get their early so you wont have to wait
I always love the bongo room for the atmosphere,  the great coffee,  and breakfast.  Love the eggs Benedict or the white chocolate pretzel pancakes.
Still the best breakfast in Chicago!!
Great food
It finds the sweet spot between traditional and innovative brunch options. Also, how is it this affordable? Loved it when family lived nearby and we’d come visit
Delicious!
Awesome food, excellent service.
Amazing pancakes!
BlackBerry Vanilla french toast was delicious. Great coffee too!
I left in awe! The food was nothing short of amazing. Definitely a must visit spot for breakfast/brunch in Chicago.

Best place for breakfast in the wicker Park area, it's a noisy atmosphere, and you may need to wait a short time to be seated but it's very much worth it, the specialty weekend menu items are delicious whether you go savory or sweet
Good ears. Wish there was more room for larger group had eat seated at one table was very tight...
We lived in this neighborhood 10 years ago, it’s so wonderful to come back and find our favorite brunch spot even better than we remembered.
Excellent breakfast, crowded but worth the wait
Noisy, crowded, expensive, long wait...but good coffee.
Good service, good food.
Service was top notch and amazing, food and drinks wonderful as well. 10/10 would go back when I come back to town.

Went here for lunch yesterday. Such a wonderful spot! They serve intelligentsia coffee and the food is delicious. My friend got the breakfast burrito and I got the chicken salad sandwich. Both meals are highly recommendable. The staff is super welcoming and helpful. Definitely a favorite spot.
Great for brunch!
This spot constantly delivers. They have good food for fair rates, there no long wait even when they are packed.

Stopped in here for breakfast with a friend. We both ordered the vegetarian croissant with a side of bacon. It was fresh, flavorful, and delicious. Highly recommend! This is a hip spot to grab a great breakfast in wicker park.
Great service and great food! Will definitely go back again.
Best Breakfast and Lunch
Just the best breakfast in town. Pancakes are outta sight as well as super good breakfast burritos.
My new favorite brunch spot. Everything was perfectly made.
Amazing food. Would go back all the time even though we aren't close.
I love the bongo room food is delicious. I love getting though omelette make your own I get blue cheese  avocado spinach omelette.
Best brunch and mimosas
Huge portions, nice service
Great food
Love their white chocolate caramel pretzel pancakes
Great coffee but just OK food.
Used to be a good breakfast place, but I think they've gotten pretty sloppy the last 10 months
Great spot, very popular, not tons of healthy options but really fun brunch drinks and sweets

Ordered the Blueberry and Almond pancakes, two scrambled eggs and chicken sausage. My waitress Jessica was really nice. This place is on a busy street so it's hard to find a park, you also have to pay for parking 2hr max = $4. Keep that in mind when it's the weekend. This place was busy and loud, luckily I came solo. I was able to be seated immediately.
Delicious french toast and hot cakes. Love the variety of mimosas.

I LOVE this little spot!The space itself is extremely inviting and well-put-together -- the music, ambience and aesthetics are all amazing. I  had a cup of some of the richest, highest-quality coffee I've tasted in a long time, coupled with an unforgettable blueberry muffin...both were so good, in fact, that I bought a second round of each to take home to my roommate!
Love the food here.
(Translated by Google) Very good place all very rich  (Original) Muy buen lugar todo muy rico
I was visiting from Texas and enjoyed very much. The ingredients for fresh the pizza was great and not greasy
Great food! Sometimes the wait is too long but it's worth it.
Hit or miss. Lately miss. Stale croissant. Eggs like McDonald's. Overpriced af. Long waits. Hipster hype.
Come for the hungover hipster watching/judging. Stay for the attentive service and heroic portions.
Great place for brunch.  Creative menu options. Pancakes are legit.
I loved the coffee. The food was delicious and there was a lot of it. Overall it's a great place to hang out and grab a good meal.
One of my favorites.
Look at these flapjacks! Look! Omg... makes my mouth water and diabetes flair up! Heaven on a plate! Oh the other dish was what I ordered. I ate that too. No fat jokes please.
Food is always amazing at bongo room

The food is great and so was the pomegranate pear mimosa. We waited about 20 minutes for a party of 2. Not a big deal. The service was great until I paid the bill and left a tip. I still had about a quarter of my mimosa left and it was clear we weren't welcomed anymore. It was about 12:30 at this point and very few, if any, people waiting. Don't think I'll be returning to this location...
Great service and the food was quite tasty.
Very creative foods
This is where I take friends and we've never been disappointed!
The food was good as was the service
Awesome food, nice atmosphere. My wife and I came here from a recommendation, definitely glad we did!  We shared the white chocolate and mixed berry french toast, it was amazing!
American food... so fresh. i look forward to going back again. the place has a cool atmosphere.
Great place
Great food, great staff! Must do!
Tasty brunch and affordable. Huge portions.
I love the food. I live in Indiana so when I come to visit my family it's one of my fav breakfast spots 😍😍 😍

Amazing food, great service, correct quoted wait time. Wormhole next door is a great place to drink coffee and wait, Bongo Room will text you when your place in line is up! Couldn’t ask for a better deal.

It's definitely worth the hype. Breakfast was excellent and can't wait to go back to Chicago to go there again. Wait staff was very friendly and I'm a stickler for good coffee and they passed the test. We got there right before the long wait for a table and sat at the window..it was tight but cozy on a cold day.
We showed up right at 9 on a Sunday and got a table no problem.  The omelette was great but the almond pancakes did not live up to the hype.
I'm not sure why, but they have the best breakfast potatoes of all.
Drove 3 hours from Indiana to eat their delicious pancakes and egg benedict. Totally worth the trip lol. The staff were nice and attentive.
Delicious brunch foods with loose leaf tea.

Loved the place. The queue starts at 7 am and the place opens at 8, I think. But it's worth the wait. If you don't wait in the queue, it'll take about 20 minutes to get a table. The food is just great! And so, is the coffee.
This is your place for some excellent breakfast options, including some rather crazy spins on pancakes.
Different infused food
Best brunch I’ve had in the city!
Just ok. Too expensive and a rush to get us out and on to the next.
Awesome spot for breakfast
Delicious brunch! Usually a bit of a wait but if you add your name in and then go shop in the area, time flies. The eggs benny are always my go to!
A very unique Tiki bar in the middle of Downtown Chicago. Not the kind of place you expect when you enter!
Delicious food with lots of brunch options - there might be a wait, though
Great food
Never had a bad breakfast. Love all the pancakes!
Delicious
Great breakfast in Wicker Park! I took my sister here the other day and we were full for hours after it was so great!
Service was fast and attentive. Food was on the bland side but portions were generous. Some of the potatos were overcooked and inedible.
There was a beard hair on the food and didn’t have time to wait for another to be made. Didn’t offer to take off a drink and was very rude about the situation.
Good grub hub grub
Amazing brunch spot!!
This place never disappoints! Great food, great people, and a wonderful atmosphere. The brunch menu is superb!
Some of the wildest pancake creations I've seen! Amazing food and great ambiance. Worth the wait, but be prepared for it!
We have visited here three times in one year. Each trip to the city we try to go. It’s good food! Staff seems stressed and not excellent because of that. But, we will still go back.

Excellent food and service! Prices commensurate with quality and quantity. Very loud like many places so it's not a place for quiet conversation. First time diner, will definitely go back! P. S. Excellent chorizo!
been here 3 times now. food and service very average. not worth the wait for me.
Great food... Always crowded... Get there early and enjoy!!!...

I had been looking forward to trying this place out for some time now. After waiting about 35-40 min to be seated (which is no problem) my friend and I sat and perused the menu. We really wanted to try some pancakes but were unsure if we would have room so ordered our normal savory fair first. My eggs Benedict was very delicious..that’s for sure. After finishing our plates we saw the table next to us receive a single pretzel pancake and we decided we had to try it. We asked the waitress for one and she replied that she thought there was an hour wait and needed to check if we could order that. My friend and I looked at each other with confusion. When she returned to the table she stated...”actually it’s an hour and a half wait and the kitchen is behind so I will not be able to put that in for you.”  It was the weirdest thing that ever happened. To be a customer in a restaurant...seated at a table and be denied something for any reason other than the ingredients being unavailable was insane. Wait aside, guests should always be served.  One star because the eggs Benedict was good. I certainly will not return.
Don't underestimate the white chocolate pretzel Carmel pancakes
Awesome food... atmosphere is a complete win
Best breakfast burrito of my life... Get the chorizo!
Love this place. Perfect breakfast food.
Had the chorizo omelette with avocados and potatoes stuffed inside. Was okay but not an outstanding omelette. Brunch was extremely busy so be prepared for a wait.

Reliably consistent & delicious - sweet or savory, but I think their sweet items are significantly better than anywhere else. Multiple different drink options. Recommend the potatoes with white cheddar as a side & any pancake with their homemade sauces 😍 their chorizo is very rich in flavor
Yummy food long wait
The atmosphere was nice, the pancakes and french toast was good, but the chocolate sauce on top made it a little to much. The experience was nice but its not a place I would go to alot.
Great breakfast burrito and epic white chocolate caramel pretzel pancakes...

Their lobster eggs benedict is a must try! The service is always good and their dulce de leche pancakes are even better! Also had their chai latte, and let me just say, blows Starbucks out of the water!

Honestly i think this place doesn’t get enough attention like it should. I love sweets. I’m a huge fan of the red velvet pancakes but i get undecided with the pretzel pancake. HOW DID THEY DO IT? It’s small, cozy. And great for a breakfast date. mimosas are perfect. Try them out and don’t forget to ask for the breakfast potatoes and cheese please!
Good food and larger portions. No gluten-free options at all, they won’t even do lettuce wrapped sandwiches or substitute anything for it so that sucked. Paying for bread when I can’t even eat it.

We come here often, my husband always gets the lobster Benedict!  I on the other hand have tried a few things but am intimidated by the portions.  I don’t order some of the more popular item for fear that half of it I’ll end up in the trash; I wish they had half portions.
Fabulous

My wife and I love Bongo Room! We come a few times a year. Today I had the best pancakes I’ve ever had!! The pumpkin spice pancakes are a 12 out of 10!!! The wait is normally pretty long, but today we were able to walk right in. I highly recommend the bongo room to all the locals and tourists.

After getting brunch here multiple times, I have yet to be even remotely disappointed. The food is absolutely delicious and priced very fairly (especially for being in the heart of Wicker Park). Be aware that there is most always a wait during brunch hours. The wait is 100% worth it. If you have a sweet tooth I highly recommend the White Chocolate and Caramel Pretzel Pancakes!
BEST french toast I have ever had!! Be sure not to miss out and order the Churro Pear French Toast 💛
The pancakes were awesome. Had pumpkin spice. Had them before. Is always crowded. Service was great. Next time will something else other than pancakes.
Great ambience. The Chocolate Tower French toast is a must try for chocolate lovers.
Was visiting Chicago for the weekend with my daughter.  This place was amazing....gonna try to go there every time we visit now
Loved it! Cheap and the food is great. The waitresses are also and extremely chill and attentive; same goes for the busboy's.
Very crowded breakfast/brunch place. The food was good but not anything extraordinary.
It's nothing special.

I went there on Wednesday, It was about hour and 45 minutes Waite.  We order Omelet, Benedict  and also French toast. They all was OK. Nothing especial about this place. I think it is over Rate. I'll never come back again and I would not recommend to anyone to wait that much for nothing especial.
Good food, extensive menu, and we only had to wait 25 minutes for a table!
Delicious food always
Pretty good food
Food was good, not too expensive and the service was good. The place is rather narrow and tends to get packed during the weekend  brunch hour.
It was busy but definitely worth the wait.  Wonderful breakfast.  The carmelized pear french toast was heaven!  We'll definitely eat there again when we visit Chicago.

Nothing overly special. Pretty long wait for brunch for two. The menu didn’t strike me as being very fantastic or interesting and there was nothing memorable about the atmosphere. They did meet the basic requirements of being clean enough and friendly staff and decent food.

Horrible. I don't get the hype. Every time I come here I'm always disappointed in the food and the prices. Why do you serve house potatoes with a potato and chorizo omelette,???  The avocado was non existent   they comped my breakfast because it was horrible but I was so hungry. Husband had pear and churro French toast.  Sure...I love having a full cup of sugar mush poured down my throat at 9 am. Save your money and your time...go to Windy City cafe or cornerstone cafe. You'll be a lot happier
Haven't been there in a couple of years. Food is still amazing. My favorite brunch place to go to. My mouth always has a orgasim. 😁👍
Good but over ratted.

The portions are gigantic and everything is as fresh as can be. The service is decent, they get really busy so I cut them a little slack. Anytime I find myself in Chicago I make sure to get brunch at Bongo Room.
Really good food. Kinda pricey but their portions dont skimp!! And the pancakes are so very good!!

This place was hoping, we were able to get a seat in about 20 minutes. The breakfast was good, the deserts were served over bread and while they tasted good. They would have been better suited over a pancake instead of a piece of non toasted bread.  Eggs benedict was good, wish it was served warmer.
Lovely
Great food, wonderful vibe,  excellent service!
One of my favorite places to have brunch/lunch in the neighborhood. Has been around forever for good reason.
Food and service was great , prices a tad rough but worth it !
Always a solid go-to! Love it!
I came back again after four years. Really delicious
Had the charizo omlete with fried potatoes english muffin and bacon. Super yummy. It was a full house and they don't take reservations or seat you till everyone is there.👌

If you're a hipster looking to take your parents to a more expensive, crowded IHOP - then this is the place for you. For the rest of us, we'll stick to Lulu.  Some of the pics you'll see in this listing are as fake as what you'll find on a Burger King advertisement. Truly disappointing.
Diner was nearly empty when we ate there so no excuses for the long wait for food to arrive. Simple eggs dish was disappointing and not as ordered. Coffee was decent.
Great food and nice location 👌
Have been coming here since the year it opened. Still great for brunch.
Awesome place! Great food!

I had the Chorizo Potato & Guacamole Omelette. The home fries were perfectly cooked. A bit crispy on the outside but still soft inside. Seasoned well with a hint of dill. The omelette was really well made. They we're generous with the ingredients! The chorizo was great. The included salsa had a nice kick and really complimented the dish.  The staff were very accommodating and attentive. Before we sat down the gentleman behind the bar had our waters. Our glasses were always refilled before empty, and we never felt rushed by our server.  Overall a great breakfast experience.
Big portions. Great food. Great service
A Bucktown favorite for the fam!
Delicious brunch, be prepared to wait to enjoy  creative old favs like French toast and eggs Benedict
Pancakes are the best. Kind and nice people.

Cute cafe with traditional breakfast options. Spacious bar counter and variety of table sizes. Was worried that such a prime location would draw lines but moved quickly. The sweet options slightly outweighed the savory and most were meat heavy aside from build your own omelet or traditional eggs any style.

The triple berry churro french toast and the tenderloin eggs benedict were pretty amazing. And then I had an awesome housemade titos bloody mary. My wife had an awesome raspberry pear mimosa. This place was recommended to us by my cousin who lives here and we're visiting from Seattle. My cousin definitely gave us the right recommendation for brunch. Delicious!
This ppl think they 5 star restaurant they will not sit u until everyone in your party is in so they made 6 ppl to wait other 2 (( not bad food but not worth the hassle
One of the best breakfast places in Chicago. The pancakes are a bit sweet, but delishious.
Amazing breakfast and brunch.
After all these years the food is still great. Chocolate French toast never disappoints. Waited a bit as expected on a Sunday morning but it was well worth it.
LEMON PANCAKES!!! Thank you for that, Bongo Room--they were quite delightful!
It's was fabulous the food & the service was excellent.
Alright. Not worth the 25$
Great food service and pancakes 30 min wait time but worth it
Excellent. Food delicious with custom items and bloody Mary's tasty. Great local neighborhood establishment.
Very good pancakes.
Brunch on the weekends is amazing but super busy, get there early! During the week is definately more calm and you can still get the best blackberry and lemon pancakes (this season)
Server was slow and inattentive, got our food before our drinks, food came out borderline cold... I'm sure it would have tasted great if it arrived hot
We had one of the best brunch experiences here! We shared sweet and savory dishes. My favorite was the deconstructed lobster eggs Benedict. Highly recommend this to anyone!!
Pancakes are amazing here
The shrimp scampi benedict here was great! Highly recommend for all breakfast foods.
Excellent brunch.  Consider sharing a plate on the omelette!
Delicious!
It was delicious!!! I ate the French Toast with an Irish cream coffee. If I ever return to Chicago, I will eat here again for sure!!!
Love this place!!!!
We came after a recommendation from our hosts and loved it.

Wow. Wow. Wow. Oh my God wow. You want decadent pancakes? You want savory breakfast Staples? You've got it here. The pancakes are definitely like nothing you've ever had and are a must for any breakfast order.
Had the breakfast burrito and wasn't impressed. It was pure egg wrapped in a tortilla. The irish coffee I ordered was too boozy as well.
Delicious brunch!  Worth the wait for a table.
One of my favorite brunch restaurants in the city. Their food and service is always great!
Great French style omelettes. Good service. Must try the Sweet pancakes next time I go.
Food is ok and it's over priced.
The staff was nice,  but the place was really crowded and too loud to even talk while we ate.
Best breakfast in town. Loved it!

The Bongo Room gets me every time. The egg was ordered and delivered over-medium, which is hard to perfect. Croissant light and flaky as it should be. But come on, you came here for the pancakes, let's be real. I usually get the white chocolate caramel diabetes monstrosity, but this time I tried something with lemon. This gives you a refreshing step back from the heavy sugar and allows for flavorful and fluffy pancakes with actual fruit. At least that's what I told myself. This place is an institution to Chicago.
Great friendly staff and amazing pancakes!!!!
Delicious breakfast burritos!

Spent the weekend in chicago and had brunch at the Andersonville location. Don't normally order pancakes, but the Meyer lemon and BlackBerry coulis were SO good! Highly recommend.  We'll be back to try other menu items.
Always a delicious meal! The best!

Service was fast and accurate. Egg white Reuben omelet + salad for breakfast. Friends had croissant sandwiches. The croissants were HUGE like Godzilla sized (maybe) to big? Fairly decent food but pretty bland and pedestrian.
Awesome place. Go visit
Prepare for a wait time, but it's 100% worth it. The best brunch I've had in chicago by far. And lots of interesting sweet breakfast options for the pancake lovers.
Simply the best breakfast/brunch spot that I have ever found in the city! Its quality is excellent, service is fantastic, & the neighborhood surrounding it is lively!
This is a good place to go for breakfast. They have some unique breakfast items, including several very unique pancake choices for those with a sweet tooth.
A different experience with brunch options. Amazing pancakes.

My visit was wonderful, we were seated immediately and our service was excellent. Employees were generous and knowledgeable about what they served in the menu. The food was excellent and was served in a timely manner. It was a little busy but overall, I had a wonderful and satisfactory visit.
Food was amazing!
Great brunch, went with 8 people, food came fast, and all plates were delicious!
Bongo Room in Wicker Park- delicious and noisy!
Great Brunch !

The service was great! we loved the spot and it’s location. We sat in the little windows seats which was a great vibe for breakfast. We ordered the omelette, croissant sandwich, and the half order of churros French toast. The omelette was pretty bland but the French toast was amazing! And the sand which was okay. They charged us for more than half for the French toast which I didn’t really appreciate it. But overall - good spot but they could step up in the food category. Couldve Been an off day.

This place had some of the best breakfast I have ever had. Their sweet and savory options are both fantastic. We were seated right away and the service was fantastic. Very friendly staff. The food wad prepared promptly and deliciously. 10/10
This place was amazing. The chorizo potato and avocado omelette was life-changing.

Great brunch spot with an interesting combination of very sweet and very savory options.  There is always a wait, but you can put your name in and have them text you (unfortunately you have to go in person to put your name in).  The dishes don't always seem like a huge amount of food, but I always walk away very full.
What a fun place.  The wait staff are so friendly!! Choices are many and very delicious!!!

I do not get the hype. The food is solidly average; I've had better, more flavorful and consistently good food at any number of diners. A side of bacon is $4.25 and they were the most anemic shreds of bacon I've ever seen. Not going back.
Amazing food!!! Friendly staff.

With new brunch places popping up left and right, Bongo Room definitely gets left out sometimes, but it's consistently been one of my favorites. The savory brunches never disappoint, but the sweet ones will get you through the roof. Their brioche French toast is fabulous. The cinnamon sugar, warm white chocolate cream, and tangy strawberries, blueberries, and raspberries blended with the buttery French toast so well I felt like I was eating a pile of sweet and tangy cloud! Absolutely delightful every time.
Very good food. 👍👍👍
great food. Welcoming staff. Favorite spot for brunch
Breakfast is always good here!
Good place, it's busy so there is usually a significant wait time for table
Great breakfast food, and excellent service staff that somehow knows what you need before you even ask for it!
Love this place!!!!! A must when in Chicago
Food is good, but long wait

Amazing food however you may have to wait up to an hour and a half because I went at prime time, you can though just walk around the city while you are waiting as they will text you when they have space

Bongo room is always a stop we make when visiting the Chicago area their new pancake options on the menu are amazing we first of course got our go to which is the white chocolate Salted Caramel Pretzel pancakes and then an order of their new pancakes lemon and black raspberries which was refreshing and for our Savory side we ordered the bacon egg and cheese croissant. 😋 Yummy
Food was terribly awful

The savory food is very good but the sweet breakfast options like pancakes and French toast are on another level.
